You have this:

    def logout() {
        if(request.logout()) 
        redirect(controller: &#39;Login&#39;, action: &#39;index&#39;)
    }

That is the equivalent of this:

    def logout() {
        if(request.logout()) {
            redirect(controller: &#39;Login&#39;, action: &#39;index&#39;)
        } else {
            render view: &#39;logout&#39;, model: [:]
        }
    }

That means the redirect will only happen if `.logout()` returns `true` (or something that evaluates to Groovy truth).

